::KitKat::

She looked at him with a quizzical look on her face. "Last night? 
Well, I remember going over the plans. Air, frontal and inside 
attacks. Well, sort of anyway. But one part I'm not sure about."

She felt a little embarressed.  She wasn't sure if it was real or was 
kissing him a dream. If it was a dream, she would look silly for 
mentioning it. If it was real, she would be happy. She did kind of 
like it. Oh well, she thought, best to get it over with.

"I think I remember kissing you."
She felt her face flush as she said it. Her head pounded and she put 
both hands against her head. She prayed those cubes kicked in soon.
